cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the characterization and modeling of the influence of shadowing objects on V2V communication in VANETs, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also presents a measurement-based analysis of the large scale fading process, which involves statistical signal processing and information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely category as well. The paper also proposes a pathloss model for LOS and OLOS communication, which involves mathematical modeling and analysis, making cs.MA (Mathematical Software) a possible category. The paper also discusses the importance of using geometry-based models and considering cross-correlation between different communication links, which involves system modeling and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper presents results of simulations involving multiple vehicles, which involves multimedia and computer vision, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
